    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"double-edged sword\" thing but it feels like economists always say the same thing about consumers paying more. like, isn't it pretty much a fact that free trade is better for the economy in the long run and protectionism is just an outdated way of doing things? shouldn't we just stick to the stuff that's proven to work?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
