      "content": "but isn't that just splitting the difference? like, if you look at the actual data from the last few decades, the consensus among almost every major economic institution is that free trade drives growth and protectionism just creates inefficiency. isn't it kind of misleading to act like there's an even debate when the evidence is so heavily on the side of open markets?",
